parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering coupler can cause the steering wheel to shake, vibrate, or make a loud clicking or clunking noise, leading to a loss of steering control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clicking or clunking noise when turning the steering wheel
vibration or shaking of the steering wheel
loose or unstable steering wheel
rattling or thudding noise over bumps.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the right rear control arm can cause the rear wheel to become detached from the car, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Rear wheel detachment
loss of control
careening into oncoming traffic.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unavailable Recall Repair for Service Brakes, Hydraulic (NHTSA Campaign Number: 23V651000)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of recall repair parts for the service brakes, hydraulic system can lead to a delay in repairing the issue, potentially causing accidents, injuries, or fatalities due to brake failure.
symptoms: None reported
as the issue is related to the unavailability of recall repair parts.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure due to Hydraulic System Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle is traveling at high speeds.
symptoms: Soft or spongy brake pedal
brake pedal sticking to the floor
brake pedal not returning to its normal position
brake fluid leaking within the engine compartment
abnormal squeaking sound when applying the brakes
brake fluid reservoir low
brake fluid draining abnormally fast.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS module failure can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Abnormal buzzing sound coming from the engine compartment
warning lights illuminated on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Compartment Fire due to Brake System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine compartment fires can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle is traveling at high speeds.
symptoms: Smoke emitted from under the hood
sparks coming from the right side of the vehicle firewall
flames forming from the bottom of the engine and up to the firewall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clockspring can cause the airbag warning light to illuminate, indicating a potential malfunction of the airbag system, which can lead to a failure to deploy in the event of an accident, potentially resulting in serious injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the passenger airbag warning light is illuminated
the airbag system fails to function properly
the clockspring is out of specification.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can result in the failure to deploy in the event of an accident, potentially resulting in serious injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the airbag system fails to function properly
the airbag does not deploy in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water damage to the airbag system can cause the airbag warning light to illuminate, indicating a potential malfunction of the airbag system, which can lead to a failure to deploy in the event of an accident, potentially resulting in serious injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
water damage to the passenger seat or airbag system.
